ygData.messageBody:
Hmm regular gnolls will be quite easy for you, at level 9 me and a partner
were taking on gnoll gaurdsmen (which make up 80% of all gnoll trains) that
spawn on the way to the "spiked" room when you find those to be really easy,
move on to Elite Gaurd gnolls, then Gnoll commanders. when those get too
easy, go to permafrost. I don't know alot about the other side of the
continent so sorry if this is westernly biased )

Gleeman, Bard of the 15th Chorus - Karana
If you see a shiney purple thing surfing by, be sure to give him a tell )
----- Original Message -----
From: Fun Bob <fun-bob@...>
To: <eqbards@onelist.com>
Sent: Wednesday, July 14, 1999 11:46 AM
Subject: Re: [eqbards]


From: "Fun Bob" <fun-bob@...>

In that area Dungeon-wise there are still some things in BlackBurrow by
Qeynos you can take, and the same with Paw...I'll bet you could just hang
out in the first room or 2, and just take the regular Gnolls that spawn
there. I'm level 17 and I'm just hanging out there gettin revenge for the
countless Gnoll related death. I'm on Povar as well, if you do go there, say
hi to Rolande if I'm still there.
